theorem Topology.P1_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) (closure (interior A)) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx
  -- First, note that `interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A))`
  have h_int : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
    have h_sub : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := subset_closure
    exact interior_mono h_sub
  -- Taking closures yields the desired inclusion between closures.
  have h_closure :
      closure (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A))) :=
    closure_mono h_int
  exact h_closure hx

theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_interior_closure_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) =
      interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `interior (closure A)` is contained in the right‐hand side
    have h :
        interior (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆
          interior (closure (interior (closure A))) :=
      interior_mono
        (subset_closure :
          (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)))
    simpa [interior_interior] using h
  · -- the right‐hand side is contained in `interior (closure A)`
    have h :
        closure (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      closure_mono
        (interior_subset : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    exact interior_mono h

theorem Topology.P1_implies_P1_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : Topology.P1 (X := X) A) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hA ⊢
  intro x hx
  -- Step 1: from `P1` we get `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
    closure_mono hA
  -- Step 2: monotonicity gives `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have h₂' : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    exact closure_mono h₂'
  -- Combine the two inclusions to reach the goal.
  exact h₂ (h₁ hx)

theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- First, `interior (closure (interior A))` is contained in `closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
    interior_subset
  -- Next, `closure (interior A)` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
    closure_mono interior_subset
  -- Combine the two inclusions.
  exact Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂
